text: Seskarö (Finnish: Seittenkaari) is a locality in Haparanda Municipality in Norrbotten County in Sweden. In 2010, 491 people lived there. It is located on the island with the same name in the Haparanda Archipelago. Since 1978, it has bridge connection to maninland Sweden. == References == Category:Settlements in Norrbotten County
